COMMISSIONER OF INTERNAL REVENUE v. Dwight WHITING and George N. Whiting, Trustees, and Beneficiaries for and of Emily S. Perkins, Deceased. No. 8579. Circuit Court of Appeals, Ninth Circuit. March 17, 1938. James W. Morris, Asst. U. S. Atty. Gen., for petitioner. Dana Latham and George Bouchard, both of Los Angeles, Cal., for respondents.

Before DENMAN, MATHEWS, and HEALY, Circuit Judges.

PER CURIAM.

Upon stipulation of counsel for the respective parties, and good cause therefor appearing, and by direction of the court, it is ordered that the petition to review herein be dismissed, that a judgment of dismissal be filed and entered accordingly, and that the mandate of this court herein issue forthwith.
